Schedule
School Overview
•Work in small teams to solve applied sport science problems
•Focus on Women's' Professional Football Teams
•Each group will adopt the role of the coaching and sport science
team for a professional English woman's team
•Define a performance related problem and seek to develop
intervention strategies using data to support your plan
The Scenario
Sat •Match Day
Sun •Rest Day
Mon •Previous Match Review
Tues •Next Match Planning and Intervention Design
Wed •Intervention Design ready for afternoon training
Thurs •Implement Intervention Design
Fri •Implement Intervention Design
Sat •Match Day
Key Project Milestones
•1. Evaluate data sources
•2. Select on ONE key performance area to focus upon
•3. Develop evidence on the performance area
•4. Create a short-term intervention design using principles
of Ecological Dynamics which could be implemented read
for the next fixture
•5. Suggest strategies for longer term development of the
performance area
